title: Facebook to restore news stories in Australia
text: Facebook Inc. will restore links to news articles in Australia, five days after blocking news from its platform in response to a proposed law requiring tech giants to pay publishers for their content.

title: Facebook Strikes Deal to Restore News Sharing in Australia
text: The agreement means users and publishers in Australia can once again share links to news articles, after Facebook had blocked the practice last week.

title: Facebook to restore news pages for Australian users in coming days
text: Facebook will now restore news pages in Australia days after restricting them, following an agreement with the government.

title: Facebook budges, will reverse news block in Australia
text: After a five-day standoff with the Australian government, Facebook is reportedly returning news to its platform Down Under.

title: Australia closer to passing watershed Google, Facebook laws
text: Australia's lawmakers on Tuesday inched closer to passing landmark laws that would force Facebook Inc and Alphabet Inc's Google to pay news outlets for content and could set a precedent for tighter regulation in other nations.

title: Microsoft teams up with EU publishers amid Facebook's Australian spat
text: Microsoft and European media groups on Monday urged EU regulators to require online platforms to seek arbitration in disagreements over how to share revenues with news publishers, a sticking point in the spat between Facebook and Australia.

title: UK's culture minister to meet Facebook over Australia news ban
text: British culture minister Oliver Dowden will meet Facebook this week to raise London's concerns, Prime Minister Boris Johnson's spokesman said on Monday, after the tech company blocked news feeds in Australia last week.
